Religious leaders say the government has no scientific proof that church gatherings are potential super-spreader events. Leaders believe they're being unfairly targeted. eNCA's Ronald Masinda has more. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The shutting down of churches is unjustifiable and irrational. That's according to some religious leaders in the Western Cape. READ: SA Lockdown: South Africa moves to alert level 4 Gatherings aren't allowed under level four of the lockdown. But they’re arguing churches are ‘spiritual hospitals’ and crucial at times like these. * eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.